reviews.text: A small restaurant inside the mall. Causal diner, with HK style food, but not a lot of variety/choices. Ordered their sirloin steak in garlic sauce with fries and veggies, which came with bread, soup and a drink. $66 for all that, which is really reasonable. The steak was okay, don’t expect a lot with this price, but the milk tea was really good! I didn’t expect that! Thumbs up for their milk tea!!
curry and beef brisket are separately cooked not stewed and presented lukewarm. Chinese soup is at best water plus salt. plenty room to improve.
I like to have afternoon tea as early dinner here.  You can have a variety of delicious food like fried rice, noodles,  sandwiches or curry with coffe or tea below $50.
The place is spacious, good seating!
Fast casual family dinner for neighborhood residents. Sizzling steak very popular! Spacious seating. Service standard is acceptable. Very good local milk tea. Tasty food and high value! 超抵！
